<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-16T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-16T05:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">741.61/610: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-16T19:00:00+09:00">May 16, 1939—7
                                p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received May 16—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>227. My British and French colleagues have recently told the Foreign Minister
                        under instructions that in the present negotiations with Soviet Russia<note n="39" xml:id="d34fn39">For correspondence on British and French
                            negotiations with the Soviet Union, see <ref target="frus1939v01">vol.
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                            </ref>, section entitled “Anglo-French-Soviet Negotiations …”</note>
                        their respective Governments have made no commitments applying to the Far
                        East but that if Japan now contracts a general alliance with the
                        totalitarian states their Governments may be obliged to reconsider their
                        position in this respect.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>